4. There is a class Finder which has two data members of type 1D int array and an integer variable.
It has two functions: getdata and findPair.
A. The function getdata accepts a non-empty array of distinct integers from the user and a target
difference value.
B. The function findPair finds any two elements from the array such that the absolute difference
between them is equal to the target value and returns those two elements in an array (in any order).
If no such pair exists, return an empty array.
Note: Use constructor , Use extra variables if needed , Only one valid pair will exist at most
E.g. Input: Array = [2, 6, 9, 3, 11]
target = 3
Output: [6, 9]


import java.util.Scanner;
import java.util.Arrays;

class Finder {

    int arr[];
    int target;

    // Constructor
    Finder(int size) {
        arr = new int[size];
    }

    // Function to accept data
    void getdata() {

        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        System.out.print("Enter number of elements: ");
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        arr = new int[n];

        System.out.println("Enter array elements:");

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            arr[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        System.out.print("Enter target difference: ");
        target = sc.nextInt();
    }

    // Function to find pair with given difference
    int[] findPair() {

        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {

            for (int j = i + 1; j < arr.length; j++) {

                if (Math.abs(arr[i] - arr[j]) == target) {

                    return new int[] { arr[i], arr[j] };
                }
            }
        }

        // Return empty array if no pair found
        return new int[] {};
    }

    // Main Method
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        // Object creation using constructor
        Finder f = new Finder(0);

        // Accept data
        f.getdata();

        // Find pair
        int result[] = f.findPair();

        // Display output
        System.out.println("Output: " + Arrays.toString(result));
    }
}


